hwAcl.description: The HUAWEI-ACL-MIB contains objects to configure ACL module, including ACL group, rule and acl accelerate, and query the current ACL configuration and status. This MIB module objects indicate hwAclNumGroupTable, hwAclBasicRuleTable, hwAclAdvanceRuleTable, hwAclIfRuleTable, hwAclEthernetFrameRuleTable, hwAclIpv6BasicRuleTable, hwAclIpv6AdvanceRuleTable, hwAclIpv6IfRuleTable, hwAclCompileEnableFlag, hwAclCompileNumGroupTable, hwAclIpv6NumGroupTable and acl trap. To filter data packets, a series of rules need to be configured on the device. These rules are defined by ACL (Access Control List), which are a series of sequential rules consisting of rule permit or deny statements. The rules are described by source address, destination address and port number of data packets. ACL classifies data packets through these device interface applied rules, by which the device decides which packets can be received and which should be rejected.
hwAcl.name: hwAcl

revisions.description: Add hwAclUserDestDomainName in hwAclUserRuleTable, and Add hwAclDomainNameConfigTable.
Add hwAclAdvancedPktLenOp, hwAclAdvancedPktLenBegin and hwAclAdvancedPktLenEnd in hwAclAdvancedRuleTable.
Add hwAclAdvancedVni, hwAclAdvancedIgmpType, hwAclAdvancedTtlOp, hwAclAdvancedTtlExpire, hwAclAdvancedTtlExpireEnd in hwAclAdvancedRuleTable.

Change the range of hwAclNumGroupAclNum in hwAclNumGroupTable, hwAclBasicAclNum in hwAclBasicRuleTable, hwAclAdvancedAclNum in hwAclAdvancedRuleTable, hwAclIfAclNum in hwAclIfRuleTable, hwAclUserAclNum in hwAclUserRuleTable, hwAclIpv6BasicAclNum in hwAclIpv6BasicRuleTable, hwAclIpv6AdvancedAclNum in hwAclIpv6AdvancedRuleTable, hwAclEthernetFrameAclNum in hwAclEthernetFrameRuleTable, hwAclIpv6NumGroupAclNum ihwAclAdvancedSubitemn hwAclIpv6NumGroupTable, hwAclIpv6IfAclNum in hwAclIpv6IfRuleTable, hwAclMplsAclNum in hwAclMplsRuleTable.
Add hwAclIpv6BasicSrcMask in hwAclIpv6BasicRuleTable; Add hwAclIpv6AdvancedSrcMask, hwAclIpv6AdvancedDestMask in hwAclIpv6AdvancedRuleTable
Chang hwAclNumGroupAclName in hwAclIpv6NumGroupTable and hwAclIpv6NumGroupAclName in hwAclNumGroupTable value length

hwAclAdvancedSubitem.description: The object specifies the number of an advanced ACL rule. If the number specified has been assigned to an ACL rule, the new rule will overwrite the old one, which is equal to editing the old rule. If the number is not assigned, the system will define a rule with the number and insert it to the place corresponding to its number. If no number is specified, the system will define a rule, assign a number to it and add it into the ACL. It will be placed at the end of the ACL when configuration sequence is adopted; otherwise, it will be placed based on the 'Depth-first' principle. When ACL rules are following the 'Depth-first' principle, the number of an ACL rule must be given 0 ,but it will be assigned by step automatically;otherwise,this rule will not be created.
hwAclAdvancedSubitem.name: hwAclAdvancedSubitem

If no number is specified, the system will define a rule, assign a number to it and add it into the ACL. It will be placed at the end of the ACL when configuration sequence is adopted; otherwise, it will be placed based on the 'Depth-first' principle. hwAclUserRuleTable.description: Configure the rule for user acl group.
hwAclUserRuleTable.name: hwAclUserRuleTable

hwAclUserSrcIp.description: The object indicates the source IP-address of an User acl rule.
hwAclUserSrcIp.name: hwAclUserSrcIp

hwAclUserSrcModeType.description: The object indicates ACL's mode type, Now support four state 0 Any match rule from any user group or any ip subnet, 1 NetAny match rule from any ip subnet, 2 UserAny match rule from any user group, 3 Net match rule from an ip subnet, 4 User match rule from a user group
hwAclUserSrcModeType.name: hwAclUserSrcModeType

hwAclUserSrcOp.description: The object indicates the source Port operation symbol of an User acl rule. It compares the port operators of source address. 'lt' means less than, 'eq' means equal to, 'gt' means greater than, 'neq' means not equal to, 'range' means between, 'invalid' means this operation of the rule is invalid.
hwAclUserSrcOp.name: hwAclUserSrcOp

hwAclUserSrcPort1.description: The object indicates the fourth layer sourec port 1. It specifies the source port information of UDP or TCP packets.
hwAclUserSrcPort1.name: hwAclUserSrcPort1

hwAclUserSrcPort2.description: The object indicates the fourth layer source port2.
hwAclUserSrcPort2.name: hwAclUserSrcPort2

hwAclUserSrcUserGroupName.description: The object indicates the source user group name of this rule. if modetype source is user, null sting means any user
hwAclUserSrcUserGroupName.name: hwAclUserSrcUserGroupName

hwAclUserSrcUserGroupNum.description: The object indicates the source user group num of this rule. if modetype source is user, null sting means any user
hwAclUserSrcUserGroupNum.name: hwAclUserSrcUserGroupNum

hwAclUserSrcWild.description: The object indicates the source IP-address wild of an User acl rule.
hwAclUserSrcWild.name: hwAclUserSrcWild

hwAclUserSubitem.description: The object specifies the number of an User ACL rule. If the number specified has been assigned to an ACL rule, the new rule will overwrite the old one, which is equal to editing the old rule. If the number is not assigned, the system will define a rule with the number and insert it to the place corresponding to its number. If no number is specified, the system will define a rule, assign a number to it and add it into the ACL. It will be placed at the end of the ACL when configuration sequence is adopted; otherwise, it will be placed based on the 'Depth-first' principle
hwAclUserSubitem.name: hwAclUserSubitem

hwAclUserTcpSyncFlag.description: The object indicates the code of TCP Sync flag(0~63), The invalid value is -1.
hwAclUserTcpSyncFlag.name: hwAclUserTcpSyncFlag

hwAclUserTimeRangeIndex.description: The object indicates the time range of an User acl rule. When the current time is in the time range, the rule is valid. Zero value declares that the acl rule has no time range.The invalid value is 0.
hwAclUserTimeRangeIndex.name: hwAclUserTimeRangeIndex

hwAclUserTos.description: The object indicates the value of IP-packet's TOS, It filters packets according to type of service.The invalid value is 255.
hwAclUserTos.name: hwAclUserTos

hwAclUserVrfName.description: The object indicates the VRF name of this rule, It specifies the VPN-instance to which the packet belongs.
hwAclUserVrfName.name: hwAclUserVrfName
